context: Houston is served by the <a0_0><b5_0>Houston Chronicle<b5_0/><a0_0/>, its only major daily newspaper with wide distribution. <b6_0>The <a1_0>Hearst Corporation<b6_0/><a1_0/>, which owns and operates the Houston Chronicle, bought the assets of the Houston Post—its long-time rival and main competition—when Houston Post ceased operations in <a2_0><b7_0>1995<b7_0/><a2_0/>. The Houston Post was owned by the family of former Lieutenant Governor <a3_0><b8_0>Bill Hobby<b8_0/><a3_0/> of Houston. The only other major publication to serve the city is the <a4_0><b9_0>Houston Press<b9_0/><a4_0/>—a free alternative weekly with a weekly readership of more than 300,000.
